<p>Please be aware of the Academic Policies stated in the&nbsp;<a href="http://www2.byui.edu/catalog-archive/">BYU-Idaho Catalog</a>, which determine the transferability of degrees and/or credits from other institutions. The transferability of degrees and/or credits directly affects the BYU-Idaho graduation requirements you are expected to fulfill. Some of those policies are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li>Associate Degrees from regionally-accredited institutions generally meet the majority of the Foundations/G.E. requirements for a Bachelor's Degree at BYU-Idaho.</li>
<li>Applied Associate Degrees do&nbsp;not&nbsp;meet the Foundations /&nbsp;G.E. requirements for a Bachelor's Degree at BYU-Idaho.</li>
<li>Courses (including nursing courses) from institutions that are not regionally accredited are generally not transferable to BYU-Idaho.</li>
</ul>
<p>Transfer students are responsible for meeting all graduation requirements including University requirements. Contact the College of Agriculture and Life Science Academic Discovery Center at (208) 496-9830 if you have questions.</p>
